Sec. 95.032.

CERTIFICATE OF INSPECTION.

Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 657 -

(a)

After completing

AGRICULTURE CODE

a citrus fruit inspection, the inspector shall issue a certificate of
inspection for all citrus fruit that meets the requirements of this
chapter.
(b) A person may not make or issue a false certificate of
inspection.
(c) A person may not sell, transport, or deliver for
transportation citrus fruit that is not accompanied by a certificate
of inspection.
(d) A certificate of inspection shall be in the form provided
by the department and shall state that all inspection fees under this
chapter have been paid.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1250, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

